## Overview

The current layout artificially constrains content width to `max-w-7xl` (1280px), wasting ~50% of screen space on larger displays. This creates a poor UX where Kanban boards, calendars, and other widgets are unnecessarily cramped.

**Goal:** Make all pages use full viewport width dynamically, expanding to fill available space between sidebar and viewport edges.

---

## Problem Statement

### Current Behavior

**Desktop (1920px+ screens):**
- Content limited to 1280px width (`max-w-7xl`)
- Large white/dark margins on left and right (~320px each side)
- Kanban board columns cramped despite available space
- Calendar widget unnecessarily narrow
- Dashboard widgets artificially constrained

**Root Cause:**
```tsx
// src/components/Layout.tsx:44
<div className="max-w-7xl mx-auto">
  {children}
</div>
```

This wrapper div centers content and limits width, creating artificial constraints.

### User Impact

- **Poor space utilization:** ~50% of screen wasted on 1920px+ displays
- **Cramped UX:** Kanban columns narrow, Calendar weeks tight, Dashboard widgets small
- **Inconsistent with modern apps:** Notion, Linear, Jira all use full viewport width
- **Mobile not affected:** Layout correctly responsive on mobile (sidebar overlay)

### Expected Behavior

**Desktop:**
- Content should expand to fill viewport width
- Respect sidebar width (210px expanded, 60px collapsed)
- No artificial max-width constraints
- Padding only at edges (e.g., 24px left/right)

**Mobile:**
- Current behavior is correct (sidebar overlay, full width)
- No changes needed

